title: For Sale:  .357 Herrett LONE EAGLE  Single Shot Pistol .  .35 Remington Rifle  Ballistics from a 12" pistol - pistol, scope, mounts, rings, dies, brass, bullets & original box  for $750
postcontent: Fun to hunt and shoot with, plus light to pack!Great Deer Medicine in .357 Herrett!!                     It gets .35 Remington rifle ballistics in a slightly shorter rimmed case (easy to extract), with only a 12" barrel!    The .357 Herrett is a Cartridge specially designed for single shot pistols.  It uses a modified rifle case that can withstand higher pressures, and also utilizes fast burning powders for optimum use in shorter barrels, unlike rifle cartridges that blow most of it out for a spectacular fireball and less speed.    It is a Lone Eagle/ SSP86 - this is the early version of the Lone Eagle, before the line was sold to Magnum Research.  ONE OWNER!  Single Shot, Cannon Breech, which results in a bull pup type pistol with a short overall length, and still has a 12" barrel.  No velocity loss, as there is no cylinder gap!  It won't beat you up either, due to the grip location. This one has a very good trigger.  I have taken about a dozen Whitetails with it, mostly head & neck shots.  Probably shot less than 200 times total.  Original box included.     The deal includes the pistol with the original box, mounts, rings, 2X Burris scope with Target Knobs, RCBS specialty dies,  100+ rounds of brass, and a box of 100 Hornady .358 180 grain SSP projectiles.     Get it all for $750 (includes bases too)(breakdown: $475 pistol, $225 bases +rings +scope, $100 dies +brass +bullets).Accurate, and easy to carry - I carry it on my left forearm and tuck it inside my jacket if it is snowing.It's a peach!  I bought it new about 30 years ago.  It is in pretty nice shape, with the exception of a scratch on the barrel between the front sight screw holes.     Making brass is simple.  Run .30-30 or .32 special brass into the die, remove, then trim it by about 1/4" with a tube cutter.  Do the final trim to length on a regular brass trimmer, then you are ready to load.  .30-30's are probably easier to turn up than even .35 Remingtons these days, and probably cheaper!     Come see it in Janesville.  A Face to Face transaction is preferred.  If I need to ship, the pistol  needs to be paid for in advance via a postal money order - No Exceptions.  You pick up shipping.  Sorry, it is a pain in the A--, but scammers abound on this site.     Thanks for looking!
